  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. It&rsquo;s given that the graph of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, h of x \"></span> intersects the <span class=\"italic\">x</span>-axis at <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the point with coordinates 0 comma 0 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the point with coordinates t comma 0 \"></span>, where <span class=\"italic\">t</span> is a constant. Since this graph intersects the <span class=\"italic\">x</span>-axis when <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals 0 \"></span> or when <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"h of x equals 0\"></span>, it follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"h of 0 equals 0 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"h of t equals 0\"></span>. If <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"h of t equals 0\"></span>, then <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"0 equals, 2 times, open parenthesis, t minus 4, close parenthesis, squared, minus 32\"></span>. Adding 32 to both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"32 equals, 2 times, open parenthesis, t minus 4, close parenthesis, squared\"></span>. Dividing both sides of this equation by 2 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"16 equals, open parenthesis, t minus 4, close parenthesis, squared\"></span>. Taking the square root of both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 equals, t minus 4\"></span>. Adding 4 to both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"8 equals t\"></span>. Therefore, the value of <span class=\"italic\">t</span> is 8.<p>Choices A, B, and C are incorrect and may result from calculation errors.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
