uared\"></span>. Dividing both sides of this equation by 2 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"16 equals, open parenthesis, t minus 4, close parenthesis, squared\"></span>. Taking the square root of both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 equals, t minus 4\"></span>. Adding 4 to both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"8 equals t\"></span>. Therefore, the value of <span class=\"italic\">t</span> is 8.<p>Choices A, B, and C are incorrect and may result from calculation errors.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"
